HEADWORD: Resistance frame
<hw>Re*sist"ance frame`</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A rheostat
consisting of an open frame on which are stretched spirals of wire.
Being freely exposed to the air, they radiate heat rapidly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resistant</ent>⟦br⟧
